         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Renewal of the turning triangle at Ila</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>2-2017</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="45000000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="WORKS"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>Boreal Bane AS is a public transport company with approx. 60 employees and is an operator of tracks. The company runs, amongst other things, Gråkallbanen in Trondheim, which is the world's northernmost tramway. The tracks extends from the centre of town at 10 m above sea level to Lian at 240 m above sea level. The steepest climb is 40:1000 (4 %).</P>
               <P>The turning triangle Ila, with the accompanying rails, points and rails crossing in a curve, Ilevollen north western corner of Ilaparken shall be renewed in summer 2018.</P>
               <P>The renewal includes both roadway, edge lines, substructure, rails and other super structures. The stretch is approx. 65 m long, has a double track and turning triangle, so the total track length that shall be replaced is approx. 175 m.</P>
               <P>The site area for the measures is marked on the attached map, see annexes 11, 16, 17 and 18.</P>
               <P>Climbing points shall also be procured and assembled in order to divert the tram past the site work.</P>
               <P>The site period will start 25 June and it shall be completed by 12 August at the latest.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_TOTAL CURRENCY="NOK">6009277.00</VAL_TOTAL>
            <LOT_DIVISION/>
